  "market_context": "After a 1-minute Change of Character (CHoCH) at a demand zone, price rallied with strong impulse, forming two successive bullish Breaks of Structure (BOS), breaking a supply zone, and leaving inefficiency behind.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed equal lows above a newly identified demand zone, satisfying the fourth SMC continuation criterion alongside CHoCH, BOS, and inefficiency.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst confirmed a prior Change of Character (CHoCH) had occurred at a demand zone, initiating the bullish sequence.",
    "Step 2: The analyst identified two successive bullish Breaks of Structure (BOS) and a breakout from a 1-minute supply zone.",
    "Step 3: The analyst noted significant inefficiency left behind during the BOS moves, confirming market momentum.",
    "Step 4: The analyst located equal lows above a new demand zone, fulfilling the liquidity zone criterion near the point of interest.",
    "Step 5: Based on all four criteria being met, the analyst placed a buy limit order at the demand zone (POI), with stop loss below the zone and half position size, targeting the swing high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price swept liquidity below double bottoms, triggered the buy limit order, then reversed upward toward the swing high target.",
  "lessons": "A valid SMC continuation entry requires all four criteria: CHoCH, BOS/supply break, inefficiency, and liquidity (equal lows) near a demand zone—entry timing via limit order improves risk-reward.",
